// ===========================================================================
// FEATURES — the places you photograph. The "city pins" of the game.
//
// ⚠ SPIKE CONTENT, HAND-WRITTEN. In the real build this file is GENERATED by
// scripts/gen-features.mjs from the IAU Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature
// (https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/ — CSV export, public domain), the same
// way Shutterbug's geography.js is generated from Natural Earth. What is curated
// by hand is which features appear, their clues, and their facts.
//
// These eighteen are here to prove the schema and the tone. Coordinates are the
// gazetteer's, from memory rather than from the CSV, and MUST be regenerated
// before any of this reaches a child (project rule 2).
//
// COORDINATES: `lat` is planetocentric latitude, `lonE` is EAST longitude in
// [0,360) — the gazetteer's convention and the one every equirectangular
// planetary basemap uses. No conversion, no chance to get a sign backwards.
//
// THE FIELDS THAT MAKE THIS GAME WHAT IT IS
//   nameOrigin      Who or what the place is named after, and the theme the
//                   naming follows. This is the slot where Shutterbug puts a
//                   local greeting. There is nobody out here to say hello, so
//                   instead every place teaches you something about the people
//                   who named it. See docs/design.md §1.3.
//   earthComparison Required, never empty. A number in kilometres teaches a
//                   child nothing; "two and a half times the height of Everest"
//                   teaches them the thing itself.
//   confidence      measured | inferred | hypothesis. Planetary science revises
//                   itself. A card must say which of the three it is standing
//                   on, and never quietly present an estimate as a measurement.
//                   (Shutterbug's journeys.js invented `certainty` for the same
//                   reason — documented vs. traditional sites.)
// ===========================================================================

